node.text: We are thrilled to see another one  of our Kidsgrove Athletic family take the next step from Grassroots to Academy football. Well done Lennon, such wonderful ability and really good attitude and making it to Stoke City Academy we are really proud of you. Well done to both Mum and Dad for supporting you in your football Journey. Long may is continue @kylemelv & @lozzamelv24 Very proud parents.

We're delighted to see that another one of our Under 8s has signed for @OfficialPVFC Academy. Young Rio has been with us since joining as a Under 6 and under the guidance of youth coach Mark Emery. Good luck Rio with your continuous development we wish your all the best.

Well done to our under 10 Blues for winning the Kidsgrove cup in epic fashion. Played some very very good teams today which did the Kidsgrove Branch proud. Well done to every single boy and managers Mark and Chris for their hard work throughout the season. Keep up the good work fellas. 👏👏

Our magnificent Under 7s with Manager Kyle Melvin. Kidsgrove Cup winners. Yet more trophies for these guys in the Cabinet. Some very very talented boys. Showing off some of there Silverware they have won this season. Well done boys and keep it up. 👏👏

Really proud of these boys today our Under 10 whites. Got to the semi final only to lose brutally on Penalties. A valiant effort by every single boy today doing their Manager Martin Wright and Codger and their parents all very proud.
Well done to manager Mark Emery and his under 8 colts. Another trophy and success story  for the Club. The ads won the Kidsgrove Cup today. A brilliant achievement. 👏👏
More success for our U11s. Kidsgrove Cup winners today. Well done to you all on such a fine achievement. Well done guys. All very proud of you.
Our under 12s Girls tasting more success yesterday winning yet another trophy. A truly remarkable season and long may their development continue. Well done girls. Very proud of you all.
Well done to our Under 13s. Kidsgrove Cup winners. Hugely impressive win today and massive congratulations to all the boys and Managers Johnny B and Dave W. Enjoy the success lads.
Kidsgrove Cup winners. Our Under 14s Victoria. Impressive win. Well done boys and managers Tim and Steve for a job well done.
Well done to our under 17s. League Champions. A fantastic season for them and Managers James Foster and Paul Heler. Well done boys.

The older they get the cooler they get.  Under 15s winning the City final today for the respective age group. Well done to Danny and the boys. All that hard work since August has paid off. Well done guys again doing your parents proud .

Our under 9 sharks winners in the regional City Finals. Very pleased for the players a lovely  poignant victory for them to celebrate. Very very proud of their achievement today.
#againstallodds well done guys you've done your parents proud.

The trophy cabinet is filling up nicely for our Under 12s playing up a year winning their respective area cup final. Another fantastic achievement by our boys. Well done Paul and all associated. Keep up the good work.
Congratulation to our U14s Bullets team winning the Area cup final in fantastic fashion. Well done to Tom and the players for a winning in such a remarkable game. Well done boys..

Good luck to all our Youth teams tomorrow that are playing in the NSJYL City Finals tomorrow morning.
Lots of teams with all abilities of players will be taking part and we wish every single one of you the greatest of success and most of all we hope you enjoy every moment and play the game in the right spirit come win, lose or draw.

You can never keep a good team down. After winning their respective league here they are again winning the Sentinel Cup at Stone Dominoes. U12 Girls doing themselves and our club proud. Hard work during those cold wintery nights have really paid off. What a great achievement.

The league Champions winners board is out again but this time for our Under 12s girls team. An amazing acheivement against some top class girls teams. Well done to to a wonderful group of girls and to Managers @mattmelvin79 and @clairejmassey  for all their hard work during the season.

Congratulation to our U13s boys in winning their league. Going all season unbeaten drawing just the one game. Some great games throughout the season against some very good teams. Well done to managers John B and Dave W and for everyones hard work throughout the season. 
Well done boys
Kidsgrove Athletic Supporting the @_pinksisters_ #inspiration
We love this. Make mistakes to improve and learn by your mistakes and it takes a good manager to have faith and accept a defender will make mistakes. It's all about learning
Our under 13s paying tribute today with an impeccable minute silence #lestweforget🌹
